title: Woodlan wins ACAC, Dwenger the SAC, three way tie in NE 8
text:
Woodlan wins ACAC, Dwenger the SAC, three way tie in NE 8 
By Dean Pantazi - 21Alive By Eric Dutkiewicz - 21Alive October 16, 2015 Updated Oct 17, 2015 at 12:02 AM EDT 
UNDATED (21 Alive) - Woodlan won the Allen County Athletic Conference football title Friday night, there is a three way tie for the first ever Northeast 8 crown, and Dwenger rolled as expected to the Summit Athletic Conference championship. 
Woodlan's defense repulsed Adams Central's try for a game winning two point conversion with 16 seconds left, and the Warriors took the ACAC title with their 21-20 win over the Flying Jets.

Adams Central had scored on an Andrew Hammond to Luke Voirol pass prior to the missed two point attempt. 
Mitchell VanBrocklin ran for 124 yards and two touchdowns for Woodlan, while Hammond ran for Adams Central's two other scores. 
In Kendallville, East Noble rolled in the second half to a 28-7 win over Bellmont, handing the Braves their first and only loss in NE 8 play. 
Andrew McCormick threw two second half touchdown passes for the Knights. 
Caleb Hankenson ran for Bellmont's lone score. 
Leo joined East Noble and Bellmont at the top of the NE 8 at 6-1 with their 42-12 win over DeKalb, as Tyler Hensinger ran for 138 yards and three touchdowns and Ryan Gause threw for two more tallies. 
Dwenger completed its run to the Summit Athletic Conference title with a 49-0 over Wayne with Blake Podschine throwing two touchdown passes and running for a third score and Amaun Clark also scoring twice.
